Police Operatives from the Warri Area Command in Delta State has arrested a suspect, Randy Omovie in possession of one G3 rifle with breach No. 69021340 and a battle axe at Ugborikoko Community in Uvwie Local Government Area of the state. The suspect was arrested during a raid by the Police. The Police also arrested a suspected drug dealer, Sunny Blessing with substances suspected to be Indian hemp soaked in gin, fourteen wraps of substance suspected to be cocaine, eight bottles of codeine and ten cups of loud. The Delta State Police Command led by CP Ari Muhammed Ali confirmed the report in a statement signed by the Police Public Relations Officer, DSP Bright Edafe. The Police Image maker said, “Investigation is ongoing.”